--- !u!114 &1457693794
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1457693792}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e939807b669dc4e7f8275d4d57f9837f, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPC
  npcName: Eudoros
  relationshipGain: 5
  dialogueLow: The gods see what you have done. I suggest you reflect carefully.
  dialogueNeutral: I am Eudoros, servant of Zeus. The gods watch all who walk this
    city. Remember that.
  dialogueFriendly: "Your piety does not go unnoticed \u2014 by me or by the gods."
  dialogueClose: In all my years serving Zeus, few have shown the devotion you have.
    You honour Athens.
  dialogueFestivalGeneric: Every festival is an opportunity to draw closer to the
    divine. Do not waste it.
  dialogueCityDionysia: 
  dialogueThargelia: Apollo demands purity. I have spent the morning in ritual. The
    city feels cleaner for it.
  dialoguePanathenaia: "I lead the procession this year. The weight of the city's
    faith is not a burden \u2014 it is an honour."
  dialogueHephaestia: 
  dialogueThesmophoria: 
  dialoguePyanopsia: The harvest belongs to Apollo as much as to the farmers. I pray
    the god is satisfied.
  dialogueLenaia: 
  dialogueHaloa: 
  interactionRadius: 0.5
  timeCostMinutes: 30
  conversationCooldownSeconds: 10
  promptUI: {fileID: 450896534}
  romancePromptUI: {fileID: 0}
  loanPromptUI: {fileID: 0}
