  - type: 1
    displayName: City Dionysia
    season: 0
    dayOfSeason: 10
    benefit: 2
    relevantGod: 0
    passiveHonour: 0
    description: The great theatre festival. The city celebrates with song and drama.
  - type: 2
    displayName: Thargelia
    season: 0
    dayOfSeason: 22
    benefit: 1
    relevantGod: 3
    passiveHonour: 0
    description: A purification festival. Apollo's favour flows more freely today.
  - type: 3
    displayName: Panathenaia
    season: 1
    dayOfSeason: 10
    benefit: 1
    relevantGod: 5
    passiveHonour: 0
    description: The great festival of Athena. Athens celebrates its patron goddess.
  - type: 4
    displayName: Hephaestia
    season: 1
    dayOfSeason: 22
    benefit: 1
    relevantGod: 4
    passiveHonour: 0
    description: The craftsmen's festival. Hephaestus smiles on those who work with
      their hands.
  - type: 5
    displayName: Thesmophoria
    season: 2
    dayOfSeason: 10
    benefit: 3
    relevantGod: 0
    passiveHonour: 5
    description: A sacred women's festival. You observe with respect and gain honour.
  - type: 6
    displayName: Pyanopsia
    season: 2
    dayOfSeason: 22
    benefit: 1
    relevantGod: 3
    passiveHonour: 0
    description: Apollo's harvest festival. A quiet, reflective celebration.
  - type: 7
    displayName: Lenaia
    season: 3
    dayOfSeason: 10
    benefit: 2
    relevantGod: 0
    passiveHonour: 0
    description: An intimate winter theatre festival. The gossip flows as freely
      as the wine.
  - type: 8
    displayName: Haloa
    season: 3
    dayOfSeason: 22
    benefit: 4
    relevantGod: 0
    passiveHonour: 3
    description: Midwinter feasting and unusual social freedoms. A night to remember.
